14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 3-103a, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 3-103a. The Oklahoma Wildlife Conservation Commission
18 may, by order, authorize the Department of Wildlife Conservation to
19 issue, in addition to regular permits issued under this title, up to
20 five (5) special permits each year for designated species. The
21 special permits, which may be co-branded in association with the
22 Governor, shall be sold at public auction or by sealed bid, raffle,
23 or lottery. In the case of mountain lions and wildlife for which no
24 open season currently exists, the permits shall be conducted by
Req. No. 1670 Page 1
1 raff le. The Department may contract with nonprofit organizations or
2 charitable causes to conduct the public auctions.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
